Section 9 — Project-Specific Business Logic Rules
## BUSINESS LOGIC — DO NOT DEVIATE

# Read/Seen Tracking
- NEVER use Dialpad seen status for read tracking in this app.
- Read status tracked exclusively in message_read_log table.
- A message is "read" only when opened in THIS application by a specific user.
- Always query message_read_log when returning message data.

# Notifications
- Notifications are created by webhook events, NOT by Dialpad notification system.
- Every inbound SMS creates a notification row in the notifications table.
- Every missed call creates a notification row.
- Notification is marked read only when user clicks it in this application.
- Notification badge count = COUNT of unread notifications for current user.

# Message Threading
- Customer threads: grouped by customer_id + department_id.
- Internal threads: grouped by agent_a_id + agent_b_id (sorted by UUID for consistency).
- Thread last_message_at updated on every new message in that thread.

# Outbound Messages
- Always use Optimistic UI — render message immediately with status "sending".
- Update to "sent" on Socket.IO message_sent event.
- Update to "failed" on Socket.IO message_failed event with retry button.

# Webhook Processing Order
1. Save raw payload to webhook_events (always first)
2. Verify signature
3. Parse event type
4. Route to processor
5. Processor saves to correct table
6. Processor publishes to Redis
7. Socket.IO emits to frontend
8. Mark webhook_events.processed = true
